‚öñÔ∏è 4. Why These Ideas Persist

Historical precedent: Real conspiracies (Tuskegee, COINTELPRO) prove that distrust is justified.

Systemic opacity: Government secrecy, especially around surveillance and bio-research, fuels speculation.

Psychological defense: Conspiracy thinking can be a way to make sense of systemic suffering that feels deliberate even when it‚Äôs structural.